Name: KINA WILLIAMS
Title: SAP
Description:
Please open an incident ticket to HR-SAPAMSLiaison for the following issue:
February step increases are not being sent on the SAP to TZ interface. Details will be provided in email to team.
**Title from related Incident record IM2924739:
SAP
Solution:
Related Incident IM2924739 closed.
HPQC 6869 is covering this issue and can be tracked with updates

TZ Interface details required from User and Syam is looking into it.
We have analyzed this issue and found that logic behind comparison is causing this failure.

Current logic for creating delta file compares current action with existing data in TZ table (zced_sap2tz_mss). If Position Action Code, company code, status code and TZ transaction code are same for current action and TZ table entry, employee record will be excluded. Employees in question(we tested with below example: 10194) have same position action code, company code, status code and TZ transaction code(TZ table contains only previous rate increase record). Only difference was dates on record. I am not sure why only these fields are being compared. If this was the original requirement, your query is answered with our analysis. If this is not, we can create a defect in HPQC, close HPSM ticket and we will work on closing defect. Please let us know your thoughts.

Regards,
Syam S. Ponnada,
SAP HR Functional Consultant,
Email: syam.ponnada@delta.com
Ph: 203-550-3504

*** *** There are no other related records.  Interaction closed by Incident IM2924739

**Title from related Incident record IM2978893:
SAP EWM is down
Solution:
Related Incident IM2978893 closed.
Received call that EWP was unavailable for users.  250+ dumps in the system (Timeouts).  We noticed that SAP had many threads running but not actually doing any work.  as these threads reached the system timeout limit  of 1 hour for online users, the threads starting to dump (normal processing).

We noticed that the SAP Update process was deactivated due to an earlier error during a user process updating data.  I re-activated the SAP Update process in SM13 which resolved the EWP unavailable issue and all threads began to process successfully.

Title: SAP issue
Description:
User is  trying to open the SAP via nfuse; however, there are error messages displayed
Error Message : "Fatal exemption from ThinWire Module
Protocol error:
Java.net. ProtocolExemption"


User tried in 3 different system, still the same error

User wants to raise a ticket

Please do the needful
**Title from related Incident record IM2998407:
SAP issue
Solution:
Related Incident IM2998407 closed.
Sent email to the user to update the compatibility view settings to resolve the issue...  Also waiting for the Enterprise XML settings to get updated...

From: Citrix, Engineering
Sent: Tuesday, May 2, 2017 7:32 AM
To: Pascua, Christian G <christian.pascua@delta.com>
Cc: Citrix, Engineering <Engineering.Citrix@delta.com>
Subject: IM2998407

I have reviewed your incident … This error looks like the user is trying to access the Citrix environment using the Java Client.  There are a couple reasons where this could be the case…

1.	The user does not have the Citrix Receiver client installed on their workstation. --- In this case, the user should contact their IT department to have them install the latest Citrix Receiver client.
2.	The user is trying to access the https://nfuse.delta.com environment using Internet Explorer v11. --- There is a known issue accessing the Citrix Web Interface site using Internet Explorer v11.  The browser needs to run the site in Compatibility mode in order to detect whether a client is installed.  If the site cannot detect the Citrix client, it will fall back to the Java Client.  To add the site to the Compatibility view settings, follow the instructions below:
a.	Open Internet Explorer …
b.	Click on the Tools menu or ICON (looks like a gear in the upper right corner of the browser window).
c.	Select the Compatibility View Settings option
d.	Enter delta.com in the section labelled ‘Add this Website’ and click the ADD button.  This should move the delta.com entry down to the section labelled ‘Websites you’ve added to Compatibility View’.
e.	Click Close to close the Compatibility View dialog ...
f.	Close and re-open the Browser
g.	Navigate to https://nfuse.delta.com and logon as normal.

This should eliminate the Java error…

If you are using a Delta managed workstation, the resolution will come as a result of the Enterprise XML file (when it is updated) …  Adding delta.com to the Compatibility View Settings could still be used as a workaround but the setting would likely need to be removed once the Enterprise XML file is updated.

Please reply back with you with your results as to whether you can launch applications in Citrix or not…
